==English==

===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[הבל]] (hevel) = 'breath', 'vapor'.

====Homophones====
*[[able]]

===Proper noun===
'''Abel'''

# According to the [[Bible]], the son of [[Adam]] and [[Eve]] who was killed by his brother [[Cain]].

